  <static seed="96" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>A trail<rsq/>s total length is <m>{{\frac{43}{72}}}</m> of a mile. It has two legs. The first leg is <m>{{\frac{2}{9}}}</m> of a mile long. How long is the second leg?</p>
<p>The second leg is <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of a mile in length.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{3}{8}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is a subtraction problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{43}{72}}} - {{\frac{2}{9}}} 
      \amp = \frac{43}{72}-\frac{2 \cdot 8}{9 \cdot 8} \\
      \amp = \frac{43}{72} - \frac{16}{72} \\
      \amp = \frac{43-16}{72} \\
      \amp = \frac{27}{72} \\
      \amp = {{\frac{3}{8}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The second leg is <m>{{\frac{3}{8}}}</m> of a mile in length.</p>
</solution>
